{{Politics of France}}
The French '''Commission on renewal and ethics in public life''' (in French ''[[:fr:Commission sur la rénovation et la déontologie de la vie publique|Commission sur la rénovation et la déontologie de la vie publique]]''), nicknamed '''Jospin commission''', was a think tank established in 2012 by President [[François Hollande]] to provide reforms in public life.<ref group="TNote" name="publiclife">''Public life'' is translated from the French ''la vie public'' and refers to holding elected and appointed positions in national and/or local government</ref>

This commission, which is responsible for considering institutional and public life, made its report in November [[2012 in France|2012]] and proposed reductions in holding [[Cumul des mandats|multiple elected offices]]<ref group="TNote" name="cumuldesmandats">Holding multiple elected offices (cumul des mandats in French) is common in France. For example, Senators often also serve as the Mayor of a city or town.</ref> and in [[Conflict of interest|conflicts of interest]]; as well as the methods of election of the President of the Republic and legislators.

With the exception of a few measures on declaration of conflicts of interest or the restriction of multiple directorships, most proposals have not been implemented.

== Previous commissions ==
{{details|Constitutional amendments under the Fifth French Republic#Study groups on the constitutional amendments{{!}}Constitutional amendments under the Fifth French Republic}}

This Committee was preceded by other committees exploring the same subject, including:
* The [[:fr:Comité de réflexion et de proposition sur la modernisation et le rééquilibrage des institutions|Committee on discussion and proposals for the modernization and consolidation of institutions]], also called ''Balladur Commission'' , appointed in 2007 by [[Nicolas Sarkozy]].
* The [[:fr:Commission Vedel|Vedel Commission]], named in 1992 by [[François Mitterrand]].

== Work of the commission ==
The announcement of the establishment of the commission was made during an interview the President of the Republic on {{date|14 July 2012}}.

The commission was set up by the Decree of {{date|16 July 2012}}.<ref name="decree">{{cite web |url=http://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/affichTexte.do?cidTexte=JORFTEXT000026194414&dateTexte=&categorieLien=id |title=Décret n° 2012-875 du 16 juillet 2012 portant création d'une commission de rénovation et de déontologie de la vie publique |language=French |trans-title=Decree No. 2012-875 of 16 July 2012 establishing a commission renewal and ethics in public life |publisher=LegiFrance |accessdate=12 November 2014}}</ref>

The first meeting was on Wednesday July 25;<ref name="nouvelobs1">{{cite web |url=http://tempsreel.nouvelobs.com/politique/20120726.OBS8267/jospin-s-attaque-au-cumul-des-mandats-apres-l-ete.html |title=Jospin s'attaque au cumul des mandats... après l'été |language=French |trans-title=Jospin addresses multiple directorships ... after summer is over |author=L'Obs |date=4 September 2012 |publisher=L'Obs |accessdate=12 November 2014}}</ref> where the commission decided to take time for reflection until August.<ref name="nouvelobs1" />

[[François Hollande]] received the report of the Committee on {{date|9 November 2012}}.<ref>{{cite news |last=Roger |first=Patrick |date=9 November 2012 |title=La commission Jospin préconise d'en finir avec le cumul des mandats |trans-title=The commission recommends Jospin to end the dual mandate |url=http://www.lemonde.fr/politique/article/2012/11/09/la-commission-jospin-preconise-d-en-finir-avec-le-cumul-des-mandats_1788360_823448.html |language=French |newspaper=Le Monde |accessdate=11 November 2014}}</ref>

=== Purpose ===
The purpose of the commission, as its name suggests, was to make proposals to renovate the political field of French public life.<ref group="TNote" name="publiclife" /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/flash-actu/2012/07/26/97001-20120726FILWWW00322-moralisation-jospin-defend-sa-commission.php |title=Moralisation : Jospin ira "assez vite" |date=26 July 2012 |publisher=Le Figaro.fr |accessdate=12 November 2014}}</ref>

The commission particularly needed to consider the following items:<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/politique/2012/07/25/01002-20120725ARTFIG00572-la-commission-jospin-sur-les-rails.php |title=La commission Jospin sur les rails |language=French |trans-title=The Jospin commission on track |date=25 July 2012 |publisher=Le Figaro.fr |accessdate=12 November 2014}}</ref>
* Define the conditions for improving the conduct of the presidential election (adequacy of the current system of sponsorship of candidates, terms of campaign financing, rules for communication by candidates in the media);
* Adjust the timing of legislative elections the come after the presidential election;
* Modify the responsibility of the President of the Republic and [[High Court]]; 
* Change the electoral process for legislative and senatorial elections;
* Increase the limitations on [[Cumul des mandats|holding multiple public offices]] for legislative and deputies;
* Prevent conflicts of interest and implement ethics rules to ensure transparency in public life.

=== Membership ===
The committee was composed of seven men and seven women, including its president.

The committee was chaired by former [[Prime Minister of France|Prime Minister]] [[Lionel Jospin]].

The following were appointed members of the commission (in alphabetical order):

* [[Chantal Arens]], president of the [[Tribunal de grande instance de Paris]];
* [[Roselyne Bachelot]], former [[:fr:Ministère français|minister]];
* [[Julie Benetti]], professor at [[University of Reims Champagne-Ardenne|University of Reims]];
* [[Jean-Claude Casanova]], a member of the [[Institut de France]], president of the [[Fondation Nationale des Sciences Politiques]];
* [[:fr:Jean-Pierre Duport (préfet)|Jean-Pierre Duport]], honorary [[Prefect (France)|regional prefect]];
* [[Jean-Louis Gallet]], at the [[Court of Cassation (France)|Court of Cassation]], vice president of [[:fr:Tribunal des conflits (France)|Disputes Tribunal]]; 
* [[Marie-Christine Lepetit]], head of the [[Inspection générale des finances (France)|General Inspectorate of Finance]]; 
* [[Wanda Mastor]], professor at the [[Toulouse 1 University Capitole|University of Toulouse I]]; 
* [[Ferdinand Mélin-Soucramanien]], professor at the [[Montesquieu University – Bordeaux IV|University of Bordeaux IV]]; 
* [[Agnès Roblot-Troizier]], professor at the [[University of Évry Val d'Essonne|Évry University]], also [[Pantheon-Sorbonne University|University of Paris I]];
* [[:fr:Dominique Rousseau (juriste)|Dominique Rousseau]], professor at the [[Pantheon-Sorbonne University|University of Paris 1]];
* [[Hélène Ruiz-Fabri]], professor at the [[Pantheon-Sorbonne University|University of Paris 1]]; 
* [[Olivier Schrameck]], president of the Department of reports and studies at [[Conseil d'Etat (France)|Council of State]].

The secretary is [[Alain Ménéménis]], State Councillor.

Two members of the Commission, namely [[Olivier Schrameck]] and [[Jean-Claude Casanova]], were members of the [[:fr:Comité de réflexion et de proposition sur la modernisation et le rééquilibrage des institutions|Committee for discussion and proposals on the modernization and consolidation of institutions]] ("Commission Balladur") in 2007.

=== Compensation ===
A rumor, spread in particular by e-mail,<ref name="asi">{{cite web |url=http://www.arretsurimages.net/vite.php?id=14310 |title=Commission Jospin : fausse rumeur sur des rémunérations |language=French |trans-title=Commission Jospin: false rumor on remuneration |date=27 July 2012 |publisher=arretssurimage.net |accessdate=12 November 2014}}</ref> complained of exorbitant compensation for four months of work by members of the committee and each of their consultants, at a cost of several million francs. On the radio, Lionel Jospin,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.europe1.fr/Politique/Jospin-travaillera-gratuitement-1182765/ |title=Jospin travaillera "gratuitement" |language=French |trans-title=Jospin travels "free" |author=Frédéric Frangeul |date=26 July 2012 |publisher=Europe 1 |accessdate=12 November 2014}}</ref> several journalists and former members of previous commissions<ref name="asi" /> have in turn denied the allegations.

However, in late September, commission member [[Roselyne Bachelot]], feeling particularly targeted by rumors, decided to publicly complain.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.europe1.fr/Politique/Commission-Jospin-Bachelot-porte-plainte-1258491/ |title=Commission Jospin: Bachelot porte plainte |language=French |trans-title=Commission Jospin: Bachelot complains |date=1 October 2012 |publisher=Europe 1 |accessdate=12 November 2012}}</ref>

=== Critical Analysis ===
According to [[Claude Allègre]] and [[Denis Jeambar]], who co-wrote an editorial in ''[[Le Monde]]'' in September 2012, this commission is in line with the commitment of each of the former presidents of the 5th Republic to revise the constitution according to their taste, past presidents setting up expert committees which met behind closed doors.<ref name="critique">{{cite web |url=http://www.lemonde.fr/idees/article/2012/09/24/la-commission-jospin-doit-changer-de-methode_1764597_3232.html |title=Claude Allègre : "La commission Jospin doit changer de méthode!" |language=French |trans-title=Claude Allegre, "The Jospin commission must change the method!" |author= Claude Allègre and Denis Jeambar |date=24 September 2012 |publisher=Le Monde.fr |accessdate=12 November 2014}}</ref> {{quote|The character of the men and women is not being questioned. However, the method used makes for almost inevitable failure. These committees work in confidentiality. So, when their findings are revealed, critical thinking prevails, the controversy settled, oppositions are firing on all cylinders and the President, to calm the political game, buries everything. We will see if it is different with François Hollande, but a change in method could give him greater freedom of action and decision (translated).<ref group="TNote">Original French: ''La qualité des hommes et des femmes n'est pas en cause. En revanche, la méthode rend l'échec presque inévitable. Ces commissions travaillent dans la confidentialité. Du coup, lorsque sont dévoilées leurs conclusions, l'esprit critique l'emporte, les polémiques s'installent, les oppositions font feu de tout bois et le président, pour calmer le jeu politique, enterre tout. On verra s'il en va autrement avec François Hollande, mais un changement de méthode pourrait lui donner une plus grande liberté d'action et de décision.''</ref>}}

== Report ==
The committee made 35 proposals in its report.:<ref>{{harvsp|Commission sur la rénovation et la déontologie de la vie publique|2012|Pour un renouveau démocratique}}</ref>

On the [[:fr:Élection présidentielle en France|French presidential election]]:
* Establish the sponsorship of candidates by citizens;
* Change the method of calculating pay for public office;
* Replace the rule of equality of speaking time with a rule of equity for the time between when the official lists are published and when the campaign starts;
* Open polling places for 20 hours in metropolitan areas;
* Change the legislative and presidential elections to later in the year;
* Reduce the time between presidential election and the [[:fr:Élections législatives en France|legislative elections]].

On the [[National Assembly (France)|French legislature]]: 
* Introduce a proportional share method for the election of legislators.;
* Rewrite the procedures for the election of officials representing the French expatriates;
* Eliminate second rounds when a single person is left under majority voting;
* Ensure a fairer representation of local authorities in the Senate by weighting the votes of [[:fr:Grands électeurs français|electors]] and disallowing votes by the members of the electoral college;
* Extend the use of proportional representation in the [[French senate elections|election of senators]];
* Lower the minimum age of eligibility for the Senate to 18 years;
* Expand the benefits of proportional voting with respect to parity by increasing financial aid to political parties.

On [[Cumul des mandats|holding multiple offices]]:
* Prevent [[:fr:Ministère français|ministers]] from holding local office;
* Make Legislator ineligible for any elective office other than a local office.

On [[:fr:Statut juridictionnel du président de la République française|jurisdictional status of the head of state]] and ministers:
* Better affirm the political nature of the [[:fr:Article 68 de la Constitution de la Cinquième République française|impeachment of the President of the Republic]] ;
* Repeal the [[:fr:Article 67 de la Constitution de la Cinquième République française|protection of the President of the Republic]] from criminal prosecution;
* Repeal the protection from prosecution of the President of the Republic in civil matters.;
* Eliminate the [[Cour de Justice de la République]] (Justice Court of the Republic).

On prevention of conflicts of interest:
* Increase the types and number of government offices that can not be held at the same time;
* Legally require office holders to sign a declaration of interests and activities;
* Legally require office holders to place liquid assets in a managed trust.
* For ministers, add limits on moving to the private sector and to certain public bodies and criminalize [[:fr:prise illégale d'intérêts|illegal interest]] at the end of government service.;
* Expand to the [[:fr:Cabinet du président de la République française|Cabinet of the President]] and to cabinet ministers rules regulating holding multiple public offices;
* Legally require employees of the President of the Republic and members of ministerial cabinets to sign a declaration of interests and activities; 
* Legally require holders of senior positions in the State that are particularly at risk of conflict of interest to sign a declaration of interest and activities;
* Improve the effectiveness of existing controls within the [[:fr:Commission de déontologie de la fonction publique|Public Ethics Commission]]:
**change the terms of office;
**extend the scope of control for those leaving these public offices to all public bodies engaged in economic activity;
* Coordinate and strengthen the system of declaration of interests and activities applicable to members and officials of [[:fr:|Autorité administrative indépendante en France|independent administrative authorities]];
* Regulate ex-government officers who take a job in the public sector using regulations currently administered by the Commission of Ethics for Public Colleges and responsible members of independent administrative authorities;
* Legally require legislators to declare interests and activities for legislators;
* Make professional legislators ineligible for more government jobs;
* No longer allow members of the [[Constitutional Council of France]] to be permanent and prohibit providing any business advice to its members;
* Create an ''Autorité de déontologie de la vie publique'' (Authority on Ethics in Public Life);
* Have the Autorité de déontologie de la vie publique validate rules of conduct applicable to [[Lobbying|lobbyists]];
* Establish an open procedure for "whistle-blowing".
== Implementation ==

On 20 February 2013, two bills are presented to the Council of Minister relating to the election of senators. Their purpose was to extend the proportional voting to departments with three or more senators, as well as increase the number of delegates from large cities and change the representation of French outside France (expatriate). These laws were enacted in July and August 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://legifrance.gouv.fr/affichTexte.do?cidTexte=JORFTEXT000027799541&dateTexte=&categorieLien=id |title=LOI n° 2013-702 du 2 août 2013 relative à l'élection des sénateurs |language=French |trans-title=LAW n° 2013-702 of 2 August 2013 about the elected of senators |date=2 August 2013 |website=Legifrance.gouv.fr |publisher=Le Service Public de la Defussion de Droit |access-date=15 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://legifrance.gouv.fr/affichTexte.do?cidTexte=JORFTEXT000027734839&dateTexte=&categorieLien=id |title=LOI n° 2013-659 du 22 juillet 2013 relative à la représentation des Français établis hors de France |language=French |trans-title=Law n° 2013-659 of 22 July 2013 on the representation of French established outside France  |date= 22 July 2013|website=Legifrance.gouv.fr |publisher=Le Service Public de la Defussion de Droit |access-date=15 February 2015}}</ref>

On 13 March 2013, four constitutional bills are presented to the Council of Ministers:
* Elimination of the [[:fr:Cour de justice de la République|Cour de Justice de la République]];<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/affichLoiPreparation.do?idDocument=JORFDOLE000027174181&type=general |title=Dossiers législatifs - Projet de loi constitutionnelle relatif à la responsabilité juridictionnelle du Président de la République et des membres du Gouvernement (PRMX1306705L) |language=French |trans-title=Constitutional law relative to the jurisdictional responsibility of the President of the Republic and of members of the Government |date=15 March 2013 |website=Legifrance.gouv.fr |publisher=Le Service Public de la Defussion de Droit |access-date=15 February 2015}}</ref>
* Change in the composition of the [[:fr:Conseil supérieur de la magistrature (France)|Conseil supérieur de la magistrature]] (Higher Judicial Council), the appointment of [[:fr:Ministère public (France)|prosecutors]] must comply with the opinion of Council;<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/affichLoiPreparation.do?idDocument=JORFDOLE000027174144&type=general |title=Dossiers législatifs - Projet de loi constitutionnelle portant réforme du Conseil supérieur de la magistrature (PRMX1306704L) 
 |language=French |trans-title=Legislative files - Draft Constitutional Law on the reform of the High Judicial Council (PRMX1306704L) |date=4 July 2013 |website=Legifrance.gouv.fr |publisher=Le Service Public de la Defussion de Droit |access-date=15 February 2015}}</ref>
* Elimination of holding multiple offices between the Government and local executive office. The Presidents of the Republic can no longer be members of the [[Constitutional Council of France]] after their term of office;<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/affichLoiPreparation.do?idDocument=JORFDOLE000027174112&type=general |title=Dossiers législatifs - Projet de loi constitutionnelle relatif aux incompatibilités applicables à l'exercice des fonctions gouvernementales et à la composition du Conseil constitutionnel (PRMX1306702L)
 |language=French |trans-title=Legislative files - Draft constitutional law on incompatibilities applicable to the exercise of government functions and the composition of the Constitutional Council (PRMX1306702L) |date=15 March 2013 |website=Legifrance.gouv.fr |publisher=Le Service Public de la Defussion de Droit |access-date=15 February 2015}}</ref>
* The representative trade unions will have to negotiate before the discussion of legislation relating to labor law, employment or training.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/affichLoiPreparation.do?idDocument=JORFDOLE000027174043&type=general |title=Dossiers législatifs - Projet de loi constitutionnelle relatif à la démocratie sociale (PRMX1306701L) 
|language=French |trans-title=Legislative files - Draft Constitutional Law on Social Democracy (PRMX1306701L) |date=15 March 2013 |website=Legifrance.gouv.fr |publisher=Le Service Public de la Defussion de Droit |access-date=15 February 2015}}</ref>

The reform of the penal code pertaining to the head of state was no longer considered. For these four texts, the government wanted a meeting of the Congress in July, but because of lack of time and sufficient majority, only the project on Higher Judicial Council was discussed in Parliament, but the Senate stripped the bill of its content. After this, the Government was forced to postpone the revisions.<ref>{{cite news |last=Laurent |first=Corinne |date=4 July 2013 |title=Le gouvernement renonce à convoquer le Congrès sur la réforme du Conseil supérieur de la magistrature
 |trans-title=The government gives up on convening the Congress on the reform of the High Judicial Council |url=http://www.la-croix.com/Actualite/France/Le-gouvernement-renonce-a-convoquer-le-Congres-sur-la-reforme-du-Conseil-superieur-de-la-magistrature-2013-07-04-982403 |language=French |newspaper=La Croix |location=Paris |access-date=15 February 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=de Royer |first=Solenn |date=27 June 2013 |title=La réforme de la Constitution bat de l'aile
|trans-title=The reform of the Constitution Falters |url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/politique/2013/06/27/01002-20130627ARTFIG00627-la-reforme-de-la-constitutionbat-de-l-aile.php |language=French |newspaper=Le Figaro.fr |location=Paris |access-date=15 February 2015}}</ref>

The text on the Supreme Judicial Council was implemented in the bill on the powers of the Minister of Justice and Public Prosecutors in criminal policy and public action, presented by the Council of Ministers on 27 March and issued July 25.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://legifrance.gouv.fr/affichTexte.do?cidTexte=JORFTEXT000027751362&dateTexte=&categorieLien=id |title=LOI n° 2013-669 du 25 juillet 2013 relative aux attributions du garde des sceaux et des magistrats du ministère public en matière de politique pénale et de mise en œuvre de l'action publique
|language=French |trans-title=Law n° 2013-669 of 25 July 2013 concerning the powers of the Minister of Justice and Public Prosecutors in criminal policy and implementation of public policy |date=25 July 2015 |website=Legifrance.gouv.fr |publisher=Le Service Public de la Defussion de Droit |access-date=15 February 2015}}</ref>

On 3 April 2013, two texts are presented to the Cabinet:
* Prohibition of holding local executive office at the same time as holding the office of Deputy or Senator.
* Prohibition of holding local executive office at the same time as holding the office of Representative to the European Parliament. 
These texts were in force in 2017 instead of 2014 at the request of certain socialist.<ref>{{cite news |last=Bekmezian |first=Hélène |date=26 June 2013 |title=
Cumul des mandats : la majorité veut limiter les débats |trans-title=Plurality of offices: the majority wants to limit the debate |url=http://www.lemonde.fr/politique/article/2013/06/26/cumul-des-mandats-la-majorite-veut-limiter-au-maximum-les-debats_3436822_823448.html |language=French |newspaper=Le Monde |location=Paris |access-date=15 February 2015 }}</ref>

Following the [[:fr:Affaire Cahuzac|Cahuzac affair]], further reforms were prepared: 
* A draft organizing law on [[:fr:Juridictions économiques et financières judiciaires en France|Prosecutor of the Republic for Finance]], presented in the Council of Ministers on May 7; and legislation on the fight against tax evasion and great economic and financial crime, presented by the Cabinet on April 24; these texts were promulgated in December 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://legifrance.gouv.fr/affichTexte.do?cidTexte=JORFTEXT000028278945&dateTexte=&categorieLien=id |title=LOI organique n° 2013-1115 du 6 décembre 2013 relative au procureur de la République financier |language=French |trans-title=Organizing Law No. 2013-1115 of 6 December 2013 on the financial prosecutor of the Republic |date=6 December 2013 |website=Legifrance.gouv.fr |publisher=Le Service Public de la Defussion de Droit |access-date=15 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://legifrance.gouv.fr/affichTexte.do?cidTexte=JORFTEXT000028278976&dateTexte=&categorieLien=id |title=LOI n° 2013-1117 du 6 décembre 2013 relative à la lutte contre la fraude fiscale et la grande délinquance économique et financière |language=French |trans-title=LAW 2013-1117 of 6 December 2013 on the fight against tax evasion and large economic and financial crime |date=6 December 2013 |website=Legifrance.gouv.fr |publisher=Le Service Public de la Defussion de Droit |access-date=15 February 2015}}</ref>
* [[:fr:Lois relatives à la transparence de la vie publique
|Draft organizing law on transparency in public life and legislation on transparency in public life]], presented by the Council of Ministers on 24 April and promulgated 11 October.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://legifrance.gouv.fr/affichTexte.do?cidTexte=JORFTEXT000028056223&dateTexte=&categorieLien=id |title=LOI organique n° 2013-906 du 11 octobre 2013 relative à la transparence de la vie publique |language=French |trans-title=Organizing LAW 2013-906 of 11 October 2013 on the transparency in public life |date=11 October 2013 |website=Legifrance.gouv.fr |publisher=Le Service Public de la Defussion de Droit |access-date=15 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://legifrance.gouv.fr/affichTexte.do?cidTexte=JORFTEXT000028056315&dateTexte=&categorieLien=id |title=LOI n° 2013-907 du 11 octobre 2013 relative à la transparence de la vie publique |language=French |trans-title=LAW 2013-907 of 11 October 2013 on the transparency in public life |date=11 October 2013 |website=Legifrance.gouv.fr |publisher=Le Service Public de la Defussion de Droit |access-date=15 February 2015}}</ref> There shall be a [[:fr:Haute Autorité pour la transparence de la vie publique|High Authority for transparency in public life]], responsible for receiving, verifying and publishing the statements of assets, liabilities and declarations of interest of some elected officials, elected officials or employees of a public body which takes proposals from the Commission.

