'''''MANAS''''' was an eight-page philosophical fortnightly<ref>{{cite book|author=Matthew Lasar|title=Pacifica Radio 2E|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Yox0netoZrYC&pg=PA30|accessdate=16 November 2015|date=14 April 2000|publisher=Temple University Press|isbn=978-1-56639-777-3|page=30}}</ref> written, edited, and published by [[Henry Geiger]] from 1948 until December 1988.<ref>{{cite web|title=Manas Journal|url=http://www.centerforneweconomics.org/content/manas-journal|work=Center for New Economics.|accessdate=16 November 2015}}</ref> Each issue typically contained several short essays that reflected on the human condition, examining in particular environmental and ethical concerns from a global perspective. [[E. F. Schumacher]]'s influential essay on [[Buddhist economics]] was published in the journal.
